body:
An applicant's applicable amount is the aggregate of each of the following amounts which apply in the applicant's case—
an amount in respect of the applicant's personal allowance, determined in accordance with paragraph 2 of Schedule 1;
an amount in respect of any child or young person who is a member of the applicant's family, determined in accordance with paragraph 3 of Schedule 1 (personal allowances);
. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . ...
the amount of any premium which may be applicable to the applicant, determined in accordance with Parts 3 and 4 of Schedule 1 (disability premiums) , and
the amount of £19.48 if the applicant is entitled to an amount (“a transitional family premium”) by virtue of regulation 2 (transitional provision) of the Council Tax Reduction (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2016.
